    "summary": "I am an Associate Professor of Public Administration at Leiden University. In my research, I study the role of experts and expert knowledge in bureaucracies and policy-making at the national and international levels. I am the author of \"The Power of Economists within the State\" (Stanford University Press, 2017) and \"Expertise, Policy-making and Democracy\" (with Cathrine Holst and Anders Molander, Routledge, 2022). \n\nI have a PhD Political and Social Sciences from the European University Institute (EUI) in Florence and was a postdoctoral fellow in sociology and organizational studies at Stanford University. \n\nI am a co-director of the \u2018Power of Evidence\u2019 Research Programme at Leiden University and the international research project \u201cINFLUEX: The influence of experts on public policy\u201d (starting August 2023) .",
